Two sisters have denied kidnapping two children and trafficking them from Nakuru to Vihiga.Devinah Mutoka and Martha Afandi were accused of trafficking the children on February 4.The two last week appeared before the same court but were not required to take a plea as investigators requested more time to complete investigations and have an interpreter in court.According to the police, the boy and girl were playing outside their houses in Nakuru when the two women lured them onto a boda boda that sped off towards Nakuru town. The children were bundled into a Vihiga-bound shuttle.The two suspects were arrested in Vihiga county. Mutoka said her sister Afandi brought the children and she did not know where they came from.Principal magistrate Joe Omido granted the two Sh100,000 bond. The case will be mentioned on Monday.